My friend, you have some weird notions. Agni permeates the 14 worlds and 
is responsible for their smooth running. He can take your offering 
anywhere and not just to "heaven". In homam/yajna, we make offerings to 
various beings living in various worlds. For example, in jayadi homam 
done at the end of various homas, we make offerings to pitris, parvatas, 
bhutas, samudras, yakshas etc.

Secondly, to one who sees Shiva as the supreme being, Shiva does not 
"live in" one place, but he is the underlying reality of everything.

Though Shiva is depicted as living in smashana (cemetary) with spirits, 
it has esoteric significance. I elaborated this in a Sanskrit shloka I 
composed just a few days back and you can read it, its meaning and 
commentary at that: 
http://groups.yahoo.com/group/vedic-wisdom/message/6719

