> invited to
> fire sacrifice conducted by Duksha Prajapati.

In any homam, the final offerings made are those to Vishnu and Rudra, 
irrespective of what homam it is. What Daksha did was to break the rules 
by doing a "Nirishwara yajna". He was trying to insult Shiva and he paid 
for it. It is foolish to take his foolish act as an example to conclude 
that offerings should not be made to Shiva in fire.

